author: Sarah Burns
title: Ten pregnant women at Dublin maternity hospital test positive for coronavirus
description: Master of Rotunda says patients should be reassured there are no proven cases of transmission from mother to baby during pregnancy
content:
Ten pregnant women at the Rotunda Hospital in Dublin have tested positive for the coronavirus, the master of the hospital has said.
Professor Fergal Malone said fewer than 20 out of 1,000 staff at the hospital have tested positive for the virus. Prof Malone … [+1031 chars]
